The paper proposes a model for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The model is based on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN), which are both popular machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions that the proposed architecture could have applications in other structured prediction problems, which could include natural language processing tasks. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible sub-category.
